<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-616-538  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 616 538.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  July 2 1990 n307 p4(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Motorola plans sky net. (Motorola Inc. studies potential of globalsatellite network)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sweeney, Terry.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Motorola signs memorandums of understanding with three satelliteconsortia for the development of a global satellite network.andP;  Thenetwork, to be called Iridium, will be based on services providedby the International Maritime Satellite Organization (Inmarsat),American Mobile Satellite and Telesat Mobile.andP;  Iridium, which isexpected to be operational by 1996, will provide mobile telephoneservice for travellers.andP;  It will be particularly valuable,according to company spokesmen, in geographic areas wheretelephone service is inadequate.andP;  One of its principal uses willbe as a provider of disaster recovery communications for businessand maritime travellers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Motorola Inc. (planning).andO;Ticker:    MOT.andO;Topic:     Satellite CommunicationsNetworksStrategic PlanningSatellite CarriersMobile PhonesCommunications Service SuppliersDisaster Recovery.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>